Ask HN: Boycotting xams. What would happen to the US economy?
text:
This year I am boycotting xmas.

My small family is not rich, but we are all doing OK, so we really don't need anything.

Su I'll buy something small and inexpensive for the kids, but that's just it.

SO and I don't exchange presents, we just treat ourselves to a yearly vacation.

So, what would happen to the US economy if we all boycott xmas and didn't buy anything out of the ordinary?
